==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|sg=[[interrogative]] [[pronoun]]}}

#{{grammar}} A pronoun used in a question. In English, the five interrogative pronouns are ''[[what]]'', ''[[which]]'', ''[[who]]'', ''[[whom]]'', and ''[[whose]]'' (also used as [[relative pronoun]]s). These require no antecedent. 
#:''What'' did you say?
#:''Who'' said that?
#:To ''whom'' was that said?
#:''Which'' student said that?
#:''Whose'' question was that?

